%% Diagram: End-to-end request flow (waiting room -> admission -> reservation -> async order)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant CDN as CDN edge / waiting room
    participant Q as Queue service (admission)
    participant I as Inventory service (Redis Lua)
    participant O as Order service (async)
    participant P as Payment service

    U->>CDN: GET /flash-sale (static HTML)
    CDN-->>U: waiting-room page + queue cookie
    U->>Q: POST /queue/join
    Q-->>U: queue_ticket, position

    loop Adaptive polling 1-5s, faster near front
        U->>Q: GET /queue/status/{ticket}
        alt still waiting
            Q-->>U: position, estimated_wait
        else admitted
            Q-->>U: checkout_token, expires_in 300s
        end
    end

    U->>I: POST /checkout/start (checkout_token)
    I->>I: Lua: validate token + reserve inventory (single-flight)
    I-->>U: 201 reservation_id, reserved_until

    U->>O: POST /orders (session_id, payment_method, idempotency_key)
    O-->>U: 202 Accepted, order_id (durable)

    Note over O,P: Worker drains the queue at backend pace
    O->>P: charge (Idempotency-Key)
    P-->>O: payment_intent succeeded
    O->>I: confirm reservation (HDEL)
    O-->>U: push / email: order confirmed

    Note over I: TTL expiry returns abandoned stock to the pool.
